M. C. Astour in <i id="mwAZk">Eblaitica</i> vol. 4, Eisenbrauns (1987), <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=0Rwals-oh6kC&amp;pg=PA68" id="mwAZo">68f.</a></span></li><li about="#cite_note-37" id="cite_note-37"><a href="./Sargon_of_Akkad#cite_ref-37" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-37" class="mw-reference-text">Joan Goodnick Westenholz, <i id="mwAZs">Legends of the Kings of Akkade: The Texts</i> Eisenbrauns, 1997, <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=izhhWQEJkrQC&amp;pg=PA59#v=onepage&amp;q&amp;f=false" id="mwAZw">p. 59</a>.</span></li><li about="#cite_note-38" id="cite_note-38"><a href="./Sargon_of_Akkad#cite_ref-38" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-38" class="mw-reference-text">Joan Goodnick Westenholz, <i id="mwAZ0">Legends of the Kings of Akkade: The Texts</i> Eisenbrauns, 1997, <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=izhhWQEJkrQC&amp;pg=PA102#v=onepage&amp;q&amp;f=false" id="mwAZ4">p. 102</a>.</span></li><li about="#cite_note-Old_Akkadian-39" id="cite_note-Old_Akkadian-39"><a href="./Sargon_of_Akkad#cite_ref-Old_Akkadian_39-0" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-Old_Akkadian-39" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation book" about="#mwt134" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite book","href":"./Template:Cite_book"},"params":{"title":{"wt":"The ancient Near East: historical sources in translation"},"chapter":{"wt":"Old Akkadian Period Texts"},"author1":{"wt":"Studevent-Hickman, Benjamin"},"author2":{"wt":"Morgan, Christopher"},"editor":{"wt":"Chavalas, Mark William"},"pages":{"wt":"24–27"},"publisher":{"wt":"Wiley-Blackwell"},"year":{"wt":"2006"},"isbn":{"wt":"978-0-631-23580-4"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAZ8">Studevent-Hickman, Benjamin; Morgan, Christopher (2006). "Old Akkadian Period Texts".  In Chavalas, Mark William. <i id="mwAaA">The ancient Near East: historical sources in translation</i>. Wiley-Blackwell. pp.<span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwAaE"> </span>24–27. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number" id="mwAaI">ISBN</a><span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwAaM"> </span><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Special:BookSources/978-0-631-23580-4" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-631-23580-4" id="mwAaQ">978-0-631-23580-4</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Old+Akkadian+Period+Texts&amp;rft.btitle=The+ancient+Near+East%3A+historical+sources+in+translation&amp;rft.pages=24-27&amp;rft.pub=Wiley-Blackwell&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-631-23580-4&amp;rft.au=Studevent-Hickman%2C+Benjamin&amp;rft.au=Morgan%2C+Christopher&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASargon+of+Akkad" class="Z3988" about="#mwt134" id="mwAaU"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt134" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwAaY"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-40" id="cite_note-40"><a href="./Sargon_of_Akkad#cite_ref-40" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-40" class="mw-reference-text">
Wainright, G.A. "Asiatic Keftiu." <i id="mwAac">American Journal of Archaeology</i>. Vol. 56, No. 4 (October, 1952), pp.<span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwAag"> </span>196–212; Strange, John. "Caphtor/Keftiu: A New Investigation." <i id="mwAak">Journal of the American Oriental Society</i>, Vol. 102, No. 2 (April–June 1982), pp.<span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwAao"> </span>395–396; Vandersleyen, Claude. "Keftiu: A Cautionary Note." <i id="mwAas">Oxford Journal of Archaeology</i>. Vol. 22 Issue 2 Page 209 (2003).</span></li><li about="#cite_note-41" id="cite_note-41"><a href="./Sargon_of_Akkad#cite_ref-41" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-41" class="mw-reference-text">Botsforth 1912: 27–28</span></li><li about="#cite_note-42" id="cite_note-42"><a href="./Sargon_of_Akkad#cite_ref-42" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-42" class="mw-reference-text">Oppenheim, A. Leo (translator). <i id="mwAaw">Ancient Near Eastern Texts Relating to the Old Testament</i>, 3d ed. James B. Pritchard, ed. Princeton: University Press, 1969, p. 266.</span></li><li about="#cite_note-43" id="cite_note-43"><a href="./Sargon_of_Akkad#cite_ref-43" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-43" class="mw-reference-text">Cooper, J.S., and Heimpel, W., "The Sumerian Sargon Legend", Journal of the American Oriental Society 103 (1983), 67-82.
Joan Goodnick Westenholz, <i id="mwAa0">Legends of the Kings of Akkade: The Texts</i> (1997), <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=izhhWQEJkrQC&amp;pg=PA12" id="mwAa4">p. 12</a>.</span></li><li about="#cite_note-44" id="cite_note-44"><a href="./Sargon_of_Akkad#cite_ref-44" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-44" class="mw-reference-text"><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://etcsl.orinst.ox.ac.uk/section2/tr214.htm" id="mwAa8">"The Sargon Legend." <i id="mwAbA">The Electronic Text Corpus of Sumerian Literature.</i></a> <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Oxford_University" title="Oxford University" id="mwAbE" class="mw-redirect">Oxford University</a>, 2006</span></li><li about="#cite_note-45" id="cite_note-45"><a href="./Sargon_of_Akkad#cite_ref-45" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-45" class="mw-reference-text">Cooper &amp; Heimpel 1983: 67–82</span></li><li about="#cite_note-46" id="cite_note-46"><a href="./Sargon_of_Akkad#cite_ref-46" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-46" class="mw-reference-text">Cynthia C. Polsley, "Views of Epic Transmission in Sargonic Tradition and the Bellerophon Saga" (2012).
Bendt Alster, "A Note on the Uriah Letter in the Sumerian Sargon Legend", <i id="mwAbI">Zeitschrift für Assyriologie und Vorderasiatische Archäologie</i> 77.2 (1987).
Stephanie Dalley, <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://www.aakkl.helsinki.fi/melammu/database/gen_html/a0000616.php" id="mwAbM">Sargon of Agade in literature</a>:
"The episode of dreams which Joseph interpreted for Pharaoh in Genesis 37 bears a notable resemblance to Sargon’s interpretation of the dreams of the king of Kish in the Sumerian Legend of Sargon, the same legend contains the motif of the messenger who carries a letter which orders his own death, comparable to the story of Uriah in 2 Samuel 11 (and of Bellerophon in Iliad 6). The episode in the Akkadian Legend of Sargon’s Birth, in which Sargon as an infant was concealed and abandoned in a boat, resembles the story of the baby Moses in Exodus 2. The Sumerian story was popular in the early second millennium, and the Akkadian legend may originally have introduced it. Cuneiform scribes were trained with such works for many centuries. They enjoyed new popularity in the late eighth century when Sargon II of Assyria sought to associate himself with his famous namesake."</span></li><li about="#cite_note-47" id="cite_note-47"><a href="./Sargon_of_Akkad#cite_ref-47" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-47" class="mw-reference-text">Joan Goodnick Westenholz, <i id="mwAbQ">Legends of the Kings of Akkade: The Texts</i> (1997), <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=izhhWQEJkrQC&amp;pg=PA33" id="mwAbU">33<span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwAbY">–</span>49</a>.</span></li><li about="#cite_note-48" id="cite_note-48"><a href="./Sargon_of_Akkad#cite_ref-48" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-48" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation book" about="#mwt171" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite book ","href":"./Template:Cite_book"},"params":{"title":{"wt":"The myth of the birth of the hero: a psychological interpretation of mythology"},"author":{"wt":"Otto Rank"},"year":{"wt":"1914"},"url":{"wt":"https://archive.org/details/mythofbirthofher1914rank"},"others":{"wt":"English translation by Drs. F. Robbins and Smith Ely Jelliffe"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAbc">Otto Rank (1914). <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/mythofbirthofher1914rank" id="mwAbg"><i id="mwAbk">The myth of the birth of the hero: a psychological interpretation of mythology</i></a>. English translation by Drs. F. Robbins and Smith Ely Jelliffe.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+myth+of+the+birth+of+the+hero%3A+a+psychological+interpretation+of+mythology&amp;rft.date=1914&amp;rft.au=Otto+Rank&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Fmythofbirthofher1914rank&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASargon+of+Akkad" class="Z3988" about="#mwt171" id="mwAbo"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt171" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwAbs"/>
</span></li><li about="#cite_note-49" id="cite_note-49"><a href="./Sargon_of_Akkad#cite_ref-49" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-49" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation book" about="#mwt172" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite book ","href":"./Template:Cite_book"},"params":{"last":{"wt":"Campbell"},"first":{"wt":"Joseph"},"title":{"wt":"The Masks of God, Vol. 3: Occidental Mythology"},"year":{"wt":"1964"},"page":{"wt":"127"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAbw">Campbell, Joseph (1964). <i id="mwAb0">The Masks of God, Vol. 3: Occidental Mythology</i>. p.<span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwAb4"> </span>127.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Masks+of+God%2C+Vol.+3%3A+Occidental+Mythology&amp;rft.pages=127&amp;rft.date=1964&amp;rft.aulast=Campbell&amp;rft.aufirst=Joseph&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASargon+of+Akkad" class="Z3988" about="#mwt172" id="mwAb8"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt172" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwAcA"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-50" id="cite_note-50"><a href="./Sargon_of_Akkad#cite_ref-50" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-50" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation book" about="#mwt177" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite book ","href":"./Template:Cite_book"},"params":{"last":{"wt":"Ewing"},"first":{"wt":"William"},"year":{"wt":"1910"},"title":{"wt":"The Temple Dictionary of the Bible"},"page":{"wt":"514"},"url":{"wt":"https://archive.org/stream/templedictionary00ewin#page/514/mode/2up"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAcE">Ewing, William (1910). <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/stream/templedictionary00ewin#page/514/mode/2up" id="mwAcI"><i id="mwAcM">The Temple Dictionary of the Bible</i></a>. p.<span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwAcQ"> </span>514.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Temple+Dictionary+of+the+Bible&amp;rft.pages=514&amp;rft.date=1910&amp;rft.aulast=Ewing&amp;rft.aufirst=William&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fstream%2Ftempledictionary00ewin%23page%2F514%2Fmode%2F2up&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASargon+of+Akkad" class="Z3988" about="#mwt177" id="mwAcU"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt177" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwAcY"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-51" id="cite_note-51"><a href="./Sargon_of_Akkad#cite_ref-51" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-51" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation journal" about="#mwt178" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite journal ","href":"./Template:Cite_journal"},"params":{"first":{"wt":"Yigal"},"last":{"wt":"Levin"},"title":{"wt":"Nimrod the Mighty, King of Kish, King of Sumer and Akkad"},"journal":{"wt":"Vetus Testamentum"},"volume":{"wt":"52"},"year":{"wt":"2002"},"pages":{"wt":"350–356"},"doi":{"wt":"10.1163/156853302760197494"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAcc">Levin, Yigal (2002). "Nimrod the Mighty, King of Kish, King of Sumer and Akkad". <i id="mwAcg">Vetus Testamentum</i>. <b id="mwAck">52</b>: 350–356. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier" id="mwAco">doi</a>:<a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="//doi.org/10.1163%2F156853302760197494" id="mwAcs"